LinkedIn Job Scraper

This repository contains a script that uses Selenium to scrape job postings from LinkedIn. The script collects information such as job title, company name, location, job description, work method, and post date for the searched job positions.

Prerequisites

Before running the script, make sure you have the following installed:

Python 3 (https://www.python.org/downloads/)
Selenium library (install using pip install selenium)
ChromeDriver (WebDriver for Chrome) - Ensure it matches your Chrome browser version. Download it from the official ChromeDriver website: https://sites.google.com/a/chromium.org/chromedriver/downloads

Usage
Clone or download this repository to your local machine.

Install the required dependencies by running the following command:
pip install -r requirements.txt


Output
The script will generate a CSV file named job_offers.csv that contains the collected information for each job listing. The CSV file will have the following columns:

Job Title
Company Name
Location
Job Description
Work Method
Post Date


Notes

This script is intended for educational purposes and to demonstrate web scraping using Selenium. Make sure to review and comply with LinkedIn's terms of service and usage policy.

LinkedIn may have rate limits or restrictions in place to prevent automated scraping. Use this script responsibly and avoid any actions that may violate LinkedIn's terms of service.

The script may require modifications if LinkedIn's website structure or layout changes in the future.

Feel free to customize and enhance the script based on your specific requirements and scrape additional data if needed.

Happy job scraping!






